<entry>
<author><name><![CDATA[Dwedit]]></name></author>
<updated>2011-08-12T19:35:20-07:00</updated>
<published>2011-08-12T19:35:20-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8038&amp;p=82735#p82735</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8038&amp;p=82735#p82735"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[cheetahmen 2 repro]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8038&amp;p=82735#p82735"><![CDATA[
Cheethahmen 2, in true Active Enterprises style, is a multicart where each level is a separate 32k program and 8k graphics bank.  You can turn each level into a separate Mapper 0 ROM image, and they will play in almost any emulator (even Nesticle).<br /><br />Caveman Games also used the Multicart approach to game implementation.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Fri Aug 12, 2011 7:35 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
